args: A few days after the battle\nwith the imperial army...
It seems as though your wounds\nare largely healed, spellwyrm.
I must apologize again, old friend;\nI made no end of trouble for you.

My memories from before I was possessed
are hazy, but I clearly have growing yet
to do if I would allow myself to be so
encroached upon by black mana.
If it's rest you seek, we have more\ncomfortable quarters at the Halidom.
I cannot make further trouble for you all.
Come now, we are past all of that.\nBesides, you already showed your\ngratitude to everyone involved.
The prince knows you lost your wits\ndue to the black mana and not any\nmanner of personal vendetta.

There's no need whatsoever for you to
worry about troubling us. On the contrary,
I think those in the castle would quite like
to hear tales of your gallantry.
Even so, I fear I must decline. And further,\nI don't particularly care to make friends.
A shame. So then, what will you do next?
I will continue my journey.\nI intend to take flight tomorrow.
Isn't there something you ought\nsee done before that happens?
Was a duel with the prince not the\nobjective that took you to the Halidom?
I cannot hope to ask him for a duel\nafter all I put him through.
I explained your reason for coming\nto the Halidom to the prince,\nand he has accepted.
Do not get the wrong idea—this is for me.
I want everyone to see for themselves\nwhat true strength looks like.

I have no small amount of my own pride,
and I want them to know the warrior who
defeated me in the arena was a woman
both strong and dignified.
I want the person who defeated me to\nbe honorable and high-minded. For if not,\nthere is no value in my pursuing you.
Or does the Lord the Skies not have\nthe magnanimity to abide the silly talk\nof her defeated foes?
If you insist, I cannot back down.
This duel is sillier than a hat store for fish!\nThat prince really is a soft touch.
I don't think mere good will caused\nthe prince to accept this challenge.
There are two kinds of defeat.\nHonest ones...and the other.
All of us—including the prince—were\noverwhelmed by the Lord of the Skies\nwhile she was possessed. However...
That was not what she truly is as a knight.\nAnd if we don't ascertain her true worth,\nwe'll never be satisfied, either.
My, but you two are a couple of pugs!\nClearly the spirit of the fighting man is\nbeyond us simple court sorceresses.
I will serve as judge in this matter.\nAre the two of you prepared?
I'm going to give this everything I have.
And I will meet your efforts blow for blow.
I expected no less of a dragon's power!
This is different from when you were\nconsumed by black mana—you move\nmuch more shrewdly and quickly!
That gal's got some serious moves.\nEven in her regular state, she's still\ngivin' the boss all he can handle.
His Highness is no slouch either.\nSee how he matches her every\nfeint and thrust!
LET'S GO FORTE! LET'S GO PRINCE!\nTURN 'EM INTO THE MEAT THAT'S MINCE!
It has been some time since my blood\nburned so hot. Still, I think it is time\nwe ended this match.
Then let the next attack decide the victor.
...There. Consider yourself healed\nfrom that epic bout of foolishness.
Sorry, Cleo—but I had to give her my all.
And I have to tell you, it felt GOOD.
So where do you think Forte's\nflying off to now, huh?
I know not—though I feel quite confident\nwe will meet again someday.
...I look like I'm enjoying myself?\nHeh. That is only natural.
The prince's power in his shapeshifted\nform is still rough, but it will shine ever\nbrighter once polished.
And when I made to leave the castle,\nthe crimson knight told me something...
She said she and her allies would\nbe stronger when next we meet.
There are many in that group with the\npossibility to surpass me, and there is\nnothing quite so thrilling as that.
Now, I've heard rumor of a ruin in which\nrests a person of considerable ability.
Shall we go and test just how great\nthat power of theirs truly is?
